{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"ex5lcezatpfmu8p97fgbey7","title":"Template Strings","desc":"","updated":1687540735199,"created":1687540231989,"custom":{},"fname":"web-components.high-level-solutions.lit.template-strings","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"4fe7e5b732b82474f756501b12e216da","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"web-components.high-level-solutions.lit.template-strings","id":"ex5lcezatpfmu8p97fgbey7","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"web-components.examples.dropdown","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":30,"offset":329},"end":{"line":6,"column":66,"offset":365},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"web-components.examples.dropdown"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"web-components.high-level-solutions.lit.template-strings","id":"ex5lcezatpfmu8p97fgbey7","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/a-quick-introduction-to-tagged-template-literals-2a07fd54bc1d/","alias":"Tagged Template Literals","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":229,"offset":775},"end":{"line":19,"column":356,"offset":902},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/a-quick-introduction-to-tagged-template-literals-2a07fd54bc1d/"}},{"from":{"fname":"web-components.high-level-solutions.lit","id":"ik9twe6vf70yht7mt79j88t","vaultName":"docs"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":22,"offset":354},"end":{"line":4,"column":82,"offset":414},"indent":[]},"value":"web-components.high-level-solutions.lit.template-strings"}],"anchors":{},"children":[],"parent":"ik9twe6vf70yht7mt79j88t","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"template-strings\">Template Strings<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#template-strings\"></a></h1>\n<p>Lit incluye una librería de templating construida por encima de las templated literals de Javascript, que son las que construimos entre backsticks: `</p>\n<p>Las template literals nos permiten crear templates en el navegador, Lit tambien incluye una clase base que facilita la creacion de Web Components.</p>\n<p>En este ejemplo tomaremos el <a href=\"/notes/olp8vo3frywt998l6h1f3ws\">Dropdown</a> y lo convertiremos usando Lit. </p>\n<pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword module\">import</span> <span class=\"token imports\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token maybe-class-name\">LitElement</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> html<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span> <span class=\"token keyword module\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'lit'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">XDropdown</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">LitElement</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword control-flow\">return</span> html<span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token html language-html\">\n      Hello from Lit \n    </span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n<p>Importamos la clase <code>LitElement</code> del paquete de <code>lit</code> para crear nuestro componente. Lit espera que se implemente un metodo <code>render</code>. Este metodo retorna una template con nuestro componente. Nuestra template es creada usando la <a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">Tagged Template Literals (Private)</a> <code>html</code> del paquete de lit. <code>html</code> nos provee mas funcionalidades de templating que veremos mas adelante.</p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/ik9twe6vf70yht7mt79j88t\">Lit</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"guomymvu5xxkrbvedoncjdw","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1687570355610,"created":1687478467553,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"503e0f736c7c1d0c26ed87839ccd08a9","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"guomymvu5xxkrbvedoncjdw","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"https://webcomponent.dev/","alias":"Cory Rylan","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":94,"offset":117},"end":{"line":4,"column":134,"offset":157},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"https://webcomponent.dev/"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"guomymvu5xxkrbvedoncjdw","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"web-components.Apis.custom-elements","alias":"Custom Elements","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":3,"offset":227},"end":{"line":9,"column":60,"offset":284},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"web-components.Apis.custom-elements"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"guomymvu5xxkrbvedoncjdw","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"web-components.Apis.shadow-dom","alias":"Shadow Dow","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":3,"offset":287},"end":{"line":10,"column":49,"offset":333},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"web-components.Apis.shadow-dom"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"guomymvu5xxkrbvedoncjdw","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"web-components.Apis.content-slot","alias":"Content Slot","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":3,"offset":336},"end":{"line":11,"column":54,"offset":387},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"web-components.Apis.content-slot"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"guomymvu5xxkrbvedoncjdw","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"web-components.Apis.template"